When mamas ask how many wraps they need…
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I always recommend two—one print + one solid. ✌🏽 The print makes even a basic tee feel pulled together; the solid goes with literally everything. And most importantly, having a second means you’re not in a bind when baby has a blowout 💩 and you have to toss one in the wash midday. Bc we’ve ALL been there, amirite? 🙋🏽‍♀️

node.text: 💡Did you know that wrap time counts as tummy time? (But is, like, way more cozy and well-received. 😂) Babies loooove to look up at you and may even push off on your chest while in the wrap. It’s not a sign they’re uncomfortable! It’s actually a common developmental milestone that works all of their neck, back, arm and core muscles in preparation for eventually pushing up and rolling over. In other words, babywearing is basically a super snuggly workout for both of you. ☁️💪🏽
